    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p>From <bibl><ptr target="#pernierTacc"/>, <citedRange>1936, p. 5</citedRange></bibl>, 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#catani2007"/>pp. <citedRange>121-126</citedRange> (ph.; dr.)</bibl>, and 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#cdlBE"/>, <citedRange>2008.604</citedRange></bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>57.2028</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>109800</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Φίλων">Φίλων</name> 
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Ἀγάθων">᾿Αγάθων<unclear>ο</unclear><lb n="3" break="no"/>ς</name></persName></persName>
                </ab></div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
               </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Philôn fils d'Agathôn.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Philon son of Agathon.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Philon figlio di Agathon.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>The typology, decoration and findspot of the stele are clues for a votive offering. Catani believed that the name might belongs to the dedicant; conscious that it was 
                    a careless graffito he suggested that it had been scratched provisionally on the top of the stele in the workshop before being cut carefully below on the lost part. 
                    Conversely, as the graffito is much less careful than the making of the stele, C. Dobias-Lalou proposed (<bibl><ptr target="#cdlBE"/>, <citedRange>2008.604</citedRange></bibl>) 
                    that it had been added later on by a visitor of the small sanctuary.</p>
                <p>The photograph of the graffito is very clear and shows that Pernier's drawing was not very acurate.</p>
            </div></body>
